If using Python (Flask/Django) backend
/src
│
├── app.py                  → Main entry point (starts the server)
├── chatbot.py               → Core chatbot logic (handles conversation flow)
├── nlp_model.py              → Sentiment analysis / emotion detection logic
├── crisis_detector.py         → Detects distress keywords, triggers helpline suggestion
├── mood_tracker.py             → Logic for saving/retrieving mood logs
├── database.py                  → DB connection & queries (MongoDB/PostgreSQL/Firebase)
├── routes.py                     → API endpoints (if using Flask, e.g. /chat, /mood)
├── config.py                      → Loads environment variables/settings
└── utils.py                        → Helper functions (formatting, logging, etc.)

If you have a frontend (React)
/frontend/src
│
├── App.js                  → Root component
├── components/
│   ├── ChatWindow.js         → Chat UI
│   ├── MoodTracker.js         → Mood logging UI
│   ├── Dashboard.js            → Insights/trend charts
│   └── Navbar.js                → Navigation bar
├── api/
│   └── api.js                     → Functions to call your backend endpoints
└── styles/
    └── App.css                      → Styling

    If it's a simple single-script project (just Python, no framework)
    /src
├── main.py          → Entry point, runs the chatbot
├── chatbot.py         → Chat logic
└── data/
    └── sample_conversations.json  → Dummy training/testing data

    
